Get out! Get out! Get out!
FOX: Move, move, move!

33:44.347 --> 33:46.725
(GRUNTS) LI: Soto,
get the fuck down!

33:47.434 --> 33:49.436
(SOTO GRUNTING)

33:56.232 --> 33:58.234
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

34:09.161 --> 34:10.246
Grenade!

34:19.797 --> 34:21.257
MERRIMETTE: Suppressive fire!

34:25.178 --> 34:26.804
Come on, move, move!

34:28.431 --> 34:29.574
Go! Get him!

34:29.599 --> 34:31.476
Get your asses down. Go!

34:32.518 --> 34:33.936
Down, damn it!

34:34.771 --> 34:35.855
(GRUNTS)

34:36.438 --> 34:37.482
FOX: Reloading!

34:41.360 --> 34:43.338
Save your ammo, Marines!

34:43.362 --> 34:44.989
Only shoot what you can hit.

34:48.868 --> 34:50.286
Soto, snap out of it!

34:51.329 --> 34:52.371
Shit!

34:53.539 --> 34:55.475
COOPER: Get behind the rocks.
Behind the rocks!

34:55.500 --> 34:56.559
FOX: All right, listen up!

34:56.583 --> 34:59.062
Forty Mike Mike!
Forty Mike Mike!

34:59.087 --> 35:00.797
Go three, gunner acknowledge.

35:04.801 --> 35:05.802
Up top!

35:13.184 --> 35:14.394
KETTNER: Three on the ridge.

35:15.561 --> 35:17.522
(GRUNTS)

35:19.691 --> 35:22.193
9 o'clock, Cooper.
Nine, nine, nine!

35:25.154 --> 35:26.656
I need a Mag here.

35:31.244 --> 35:32.370
Soto!

35:34.205 --> 35:36.207
Get down! Soto!

35:37.667 --> 35:38.960
(PANTING)

35:41.754 --> 35:42.855
(GRUNTS)

35:42.880 --> 35:44.382
MARINE: Man down!

35:45.174 --> 35:47.135
Soto! Soto!

35:50.596 --> 35:52.306
(GRUNTS) Ah!

35:53.266 --> 35:54.434
(SCREAMING)

35:56.227 --> 35:57.395
Fuck you!

35:59.897 --> 36:01.232
(GROANS)

36:03.901 --> 36:04.902
(GRUNTING)

36:10.324 --> 36:11.367
Ridge clear!

36:12.201 --> 36:13.594
(MOANING)

36:13.619 --> 36:14.704
Li.

36:16.372 --> 36:17.915
Li, come on, man.

36:19.500 --> 36:20.501
No.

36:21.753 --> 36:23.421
No, buddy, come on.

36:24.630 --> 36:26.591
(PANTING)

36:31.888 --> 36:33.322
(COUGHING)

36:33.347 --> 36:35.433
FOX: Relax. Let it go.

36:35.600 --> 36:37.018
(GASPING)

36:38.478 --> 36:39.604
(SHUSHING)

36:40.646 --> 36:41.814
It's okay.

36:42.315 --> 36:43.649
(COOPER COUGHING)

36:44.734 --> 36:45.793
Shh!

36:45.818 --> 36:47.487
Let it go.

36:56.954 --> 36:59.248
Li. Li.

37:02.919 --> 37:04.295
(MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

37:12.011 --> 37:13.137
Fuck!

37:14.931 --> 37:17.016
Hey! Marine!

37:18.017 --> 37:19.477
Stand down!

37:20.686 --> 37:22.063
Walk away!

37:22.438 --> 37:24.065
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

37:24.816 --> 37:26.651
(GUN FIRING)

37:27.819 --> 37:29.445
(PANTING)

37:30.780 --> 37:32.240
(GUN FIRING)

37:35.827 --> 37:38.329
Easy. Easy, easy.

37:39.205 --> 37:40.998
Slow down. Slow down.

37:42.166 --> 37:43.376
Slow it down.

37:44.669 --> 37:46.128
Breathe, Marine.

37:48.047 --> 37:49.674
There you go.

37:51.008 --> 37:52.343
Let it go.

37:55.680 --> 37:56.806
(RUMBLING)

38:08.776 --> 38:10.528
(SIGHING)

38:15.449 --> 38:16.742
Hey.

38:17.243 --> 38:19.178
Cowboy up, do you hear me?

38:19.203 --> 38:21.247
Get back in the game.
Let's go.

38:38.931 --> 38:39.991
Corporal, we need to move.

38:40.016 --> 38:41.075
That was a coordinated attack.

38:41.100 --> 38:43.619
We're gonna have every Muji in
the province gunnin' for us.

38:43.644 --> 38:45.830
And I need to
get her out in 48 hours.

38:45.855 --> 38:47.732
We can't leave our men behind.

38:48.399 --> 38:51.544
I know what it's like
to lose good men, Corporal.

38:51.569 --> 38:55.072
But if we don't get our asses in
gear, we're gonna lose a lot more.

38:55.323 --> 38:56.449
Let's go.

38:56.949 --> 38:58.409
Senior Chief.

38:59.577 --> 39:00.595
I don't think we can help you.

39:00.620 --> 39:02.413
We're box kickers,
not a fire team.

39:03.789 --> 39:05.082
You are now, kid.

39:40.409 --> 39:43.913
Hey, Private, keep it together.

39:44.914 --> 39:46.265
Go pull Li's dog tags.

39:46.290 --> 39:48.334
Consolidate his ammo.
Roger that.

39:51.128 --> 39:53.230
Everything's
shot up or blown up.

39:53.255 --> 39:56.467
Vehicles are toast.
We got no SatComm.

39:58.302 --> 40:00.112
Let's go. Come on.
(PANTING)

40:00.137 --> 40:01.347
Thank you.

40:01.555 --> 40:03.349
Move or die, Marines!

40:05.101 --> 40:07.286
Standard diamond formation.

40:07.311 --> 40:09.730
Package in the middle.
Let's move.

40:47.226 --> 40:48.494
Set up a perimeter.

40:48.519 --> 40:49.620
Aye-aye.

40:49.645 --> 40:50.813
Anoosh.

40:54.066 --> 40:55.693
(SOFTLY) Here, drink.

40:56.027 --> 40:57.570
Thank you.

41:01.991 --> 41:04.677
Thank you. You okay?
Okay, come on.

41:04.702 --> 41:05.870
Here.

41:07.246 --> 41:08.539
Stay here.

41:10.166 --> 41:11.684
You watch her.
FAISAL: Yes, sir.

41:11.709 --> 41:13.044
(FOX WHISTLING)

41:13.586 --> 41:15.062
You go low. I'm gonna
take the high ground.

41:15.087 --> 41:16.422
All right.

41:20.176 --> 41:21.385
(SIGHS)

41:23.763 --> 41:25.139
(CONVERSING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

41:49.330 --> 41:50.539
(SCOFFS)

41:58.255 --> 42:00.257
I don't trust this Muji.

42:02.760 --> 42:06.322
He fought with us, took
the same gunfire we did.

42:06.347 --> 42:07.515
KETTNER: Still.

42:09.850 --> 42:12.269
I'm not invitin' him over
for Sunday night dinner.

42:12.770 --> 42:15.272
I don't think
he'd show if you did.

42:21.779 --> 42:23.906
(CONVERSING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

42:40.214 --> 42:41.632
What do you make of her?

42:44.135 --> 42:45.302
Hard to tell.

42:47.054 --> 42:50.307
She must make some kinda juice
to have SEALS come extract her.

42:51.267 --> 42:52.268
(SIGHS)

42:55.187 --> 42:56.647
She's kinda hot.

42:59.441 --> 43:00.651
Think I can hit that?

43:01.110 --> 43:02.319
(CHUCKLES)

43:04.029 --> 43:05.197
You're a sick fuck.

43:17.042 --> 43:18.419
Stay sharp.

43:19.003 --> 43:20.212
Soto.

43:24.717 --> 43:25.818
(SIGHS)

43:25.843 --> 43:27.678
Tough day, huh, Bro?

43:29.513 --> 43:30.514
(SNIFFLING)

43:31.849 --> 43:33.517
He took a bullet for me.

43:36.020 --> 43:37.688
If I had just done my job.

43:38.981 --> 43:41.066
Don't do this to yourself, man.

43:43.027 --> 43:45.196
He knew what he signed up for.

43:48.157 --> 43:50.034
He didn't deserve that.

43:51.577 --> 43:52.578
No.

43:54.205 --> 43:56.332
But it's not your fault.
Yes, it is.

43:57.208 --> 43:59.043
We all get scared sometimes.

44:01.670 --> 44:03.910
It's what you do when you're
under pressure that matters.

44:06.217 --> 44:08.194
Now quit your whining
and man up.

44:08.219 --> 44:09.220
(SNIFFLES)

44:13.599 --> 44:17.102
Are you ready to lay some pain for these
Mujis and make it outta here, man?

44:18.979 --> 44:21.065
That's how we honor Li.

44:21.440 --> 44:22.499
(SNIFFLES)

44:22.524 --> 44:25.736
Oorah?
Oorah.

44:28.030 --> 44:29.089
(HELICOPTER HOVERING)

44:29.114 --> 44:31.091
JONES: <i>Major Gavins.
We have a situation, sir.</i>

44:31.116 --> 44:33.761
<i>CLR 10 didn't make it
to FOB Ouellette.</i>

44:33.786 --> 44:35.137
GAVINS: <i>Where are they?</i>

44:35.162 --> 44:39.016
Well, COC reported them offline in
the vicinity of the 67th gridline.

44:39.041 --> 44:40.267
And?

44:40.292 --> 44:41.393
Not good, sir.

44:41.418 --> 44:43.587
Supply train was
totally destroyed.

44:44.880 --> 44:46.148
KIA?

44:46.173 --> 44:47.858
We brought six back last night.

44:47.883 --> 44:49.652
And here's where
it gets interesting.

44:49.677 --> 44:53.239
One of the KIA was a SEAL.
He was part of Team 10.

44:53.264 --> 44:57.243
They went into the Tangi Valley yesterday
to extract a high value package.

44:57.268 --> 44:58.494
What kind of package?

44:58.519 --> 45:00.537
What the hell's a Navy SEAL
doing with our unit?

45:00.562 --> 45:01.789
Don't know.

45:01.814 --> 45:04.959
And sir, five of our
marines are missing.

45:04.984 --> 45:07.836
Missing? Who?

45:07.861 --> 45:12.283
Merrimette, Soto, Kettner,
Allen, and the new guy, Faisal.

45:12.533 --> 45:13.592
Li?

45:13.617 --> 45:15.119
Didn't make it, sir.

45:17.454 --> 45:19.890
And the unit? You got a
fixed position on 'em?

45:19.915 --> 45:21.100
No.

45:21.125 --> 45:22.309
We have a best guess.

45:22.334 --> 45:24.795
I want a no-bullshit
assessment, Captain.

45:26.505 --> 45:31.402
We believe they've gotta be on the move
somewhere in the Helmand River Valley.

45:31.427 --> 45:34.029
We gotta get them outta there soon,
sir, or they'll be eaten alive.

45:34.054 --> 45:36.282
Well, let's not write 'em off.
They're marines.

45:36.307 --> 45:37.808
They're supply marines.

45:37.975 --> 45:38.976
They're marines.

45:40.185 --> 45:44.915
Strap in and bring everything to bear
we have to get our people outta there.

45:44.940 --> 45:47.526
I'm trying, sir,
but we can't push air.

45:47.985 --> 45:50.465
There's a sandstorm kickin' up
between them and us right there.

45:50.487 --> 45:51.922
We got red air?

45:51.947 --> 45:55.843
Yes, sir. High winds, low visibility.
Air support's grounded.

45:55.868 --> 45:59.555
I don't want excuses. Find me a
workaround and let's get this solved.

45:59.580 --> 46:00.764
You hear me?

46:00.789 --> 46:02.291
Yes, sir.
Let's bring our boys home.

46:03.834 --> 46:05.127
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

46:09.798 --> 46:10.799
Shit!

46:11.967 --> 46:14.511
Bring up grid 67,
give me weather.

46:25.606 --> 46:27.441
(EXHALES)

46:31.028 --> 46:32.696
It sure is pretty, isn't it?

46:35.824 --> 46:38.369
Yeah. It looks like
a five-star resort.

46:40.204 --> 46:42.331
Take a look at your 12.

46:47.586 --> 46:49.605
So what exactly am I lookin' at?

46:49.630 --> 46:51.924
You're lookin' at the most
dangerous place on Earth,

46:53.842 --> 46:55.928
with the toughest enemy
you'll ever face.

46:58.972 --> 47:01.225
There's a reason why
they've never lost a war.

47:02.059 --> 47:03.894
Now, look at your 10.

47:07.064 --> 47:10.067
There's a village called Minar.
It's about 20 clicks away.

47:10.734 --> 47:13.237
And there's a captain there,
he's a pretty good guy.

47:13.821 --> 47:15.464
If we can make it there
by this afternoon,

47:15.489 --> 47:18.092
I think you got a chance to make it
back to Leatherneck for a little chow.

47:18.117 --> 47:19.593
What do you say?

47:19.618 --> 47:21.036
What about FOB Ouellette?

47:22.413 --> 47:23.430
That's too far.

47:23.455 --> 47:26.225
With the heat we got on us, we'll
never make it back in time.

47:26.250 --> 47:28.419
And you can trust
this police captain?

47:29.002 --> 47:33.590
If you're lookin' for guarantees in this
country, you're in the wrong place.

47:34.800 --> 47:37.094
And the wrong war,
for that goddamned matter.

47:38.303 --> 47:39.905
Who are we protecting?

47:39.930 --> 47:42.616
That doesn't matter. What
matters is she gets back alive.

47:42.641 --> 47:44.059
She's bigger than you and me.

47:45.227 --> 47:46.228
(CLEARS THROAT)

47:47.271 --> 47:48.872
So you like this play?

47:48.897 --> 47:52.401
A midday trek through
the Helmand River Valley,

47:53.777 --> 47:57.756
humping a tier one package,
short on water, short on ammo,

47:57.781 --> 48:00.576
and everybody in this
province gunning for us.

48:02.286 --> 48:04.621
What's not to like? (CHUCKLES)

48:34.026 --> 48:35.903
ANOOSH: Is that your daughter?

48:37.321 --> 48:38.405
Yep.

48:40.240 --> 48:41.825
She just turned five.

48:43.285 --> 48:44.745
She's beautiful.

48:47.080 --> 48:49.099
You have children?

48:49.124 --> 48:50.375
No.

48:51.835 --> 48:53.854
I had a younger sister.

48:53.879 --> 48:56.548
She was killed by the
Taliban when she was 13.

48:59.885 --> 49:01.011
What for?

49:01.595 --> 49:02.846
To punish me.

49:04.515 --> 49:07.643
To punish my family for
violating Sharia law.

49:10.854 --> 49:15.526
Sharia law as interpreted by the Taliban
forbids women to have an education.

49:17.694 --> 49:21.114
<i>My parents broke with this
tradition and sent me to college.</i>

49:22.908 --> 49:25.744
When I returned to Afghanistan,

49:27.037 --> 49:29.289
the Taliban wanted
to make an example of me.

49:32.209 --> 49:38.632
<i>It was decided by the tribal elders to send
a message to the people of my infidelity.</i>

49:40.759 --> 49:42.511
But they couldn't kill me.

49:43.720 --> 49:45.681
<i>Then I would be a martyr.</i>

49:49.101 --> 49:51.228
I begged them to take
my life but...

49:53.105 --> 49:54.106
(GUNSHOT)

49:57.734 --> 50:01.905
She was just a child, had
so much life ahead of her.

50:05.909 --> 50:07.177
I'm sorry.

50:07.202 --> 50:08.203
(EXHALES)

50:09.454 --> 50:10.639
So am I.

50:10.664 --> 50:11.665
(GUNSHOT)

50:11.915 --> 50:13.333
Sniper!

50:13.584 --> 50:15.168
Get down! Get down!

50:18.422 --> 50:19.898
Where'd that shot come from?

50:19.923 --> 50:21.233
I don't know. I can't see 'em.

50:21.258 --> 50:23.860
We're going to need another round
if we're gonna zero in on him.

50:23.885 --> 50:25.095
Another round?
(GUNFIRE)

50:26.805 --> 50:29.241
He's got us pretty
well dialed in here.

50:29.266 --> 50:30.325
All right, heads down, Marines.

50:30.350 --> 50:32.603
Dude, my head is
not goin' anywhere.

50:33.020 --> 50:34.605
Give me your binos.

50:35.897 --> 50:36.898
All right.

50:37.816 --> 50:39.860
Let's find this son of a bitch.

50:42.404 --> 50:43.797
Where you at?

50:43.822 --> 50:45.198
Come on.

50:48.201 --> 50:49.578
There you are.

50:50.829 --> 50:51.830
MERRIMETTE: Where?

50:52.247 --> 50:53.932
At 700 meters.

50:53.957 --> 50:55.292
Look at your one.

50:56.835 --> 50:58.462
Do you see the glint?

50:59.338 --> 51:01.298
The sun's reflecting
off his optics.

51:01.548 --> 51:03.050
MERRIMETTE: Yeah, yeah, I got it.

51:04.009 --> 51:05.944
He's far. Danni?

51:05.969 --> 51:07.304
Yeah, I see him.

51:08.055 --> 51:09.348
Can you take him?

51:09.806 --> 51:13.894
In perfect conditions, if we
were 300 meters closer, maybe.

51:14.561 --> 51:15.681
All right, so what do we do?

51:15.687 --> 51:17.456
Get 300 meters closer.

51:17.481 --> 51:20.167
That would be choice number one,

51:20.192 --> 51:23.378
but when we get there, if we
miss, we're in the same boat.

51:23.403 --> 51:25.922
Only worse.
Because we're closer.

51:25.947 --> 51:27.157
FOX: Exactly.

51:28.158 --> 51:29.409
So what's choice number two?

51:30.369 --> 51:34.765
Well, Merrimette, we can sit here and
wait until one of them shoots one of us.

51:34.790 --> 51:35.849
(CHUCKLES)

51:35.874 --> 51:38.060
Yeah, then we all get shot.

51:38.085 --> 51:39.169
(BULLET RICOCHETS)

51:39.670 --> 51:42.839
I'm not feelin' that.
FOX: You know what? Enough of this shit.

51:43.548 --> 51:44.716
Khalid?

51:48.553 --> 51:49.946
Let's go get up close
and personal.

51:49.971 --> 51:51.571
MERRIMETTE: Not all of us can make that.

51:52.349 --> 51:54.159
Not all of us.

51:54.184 --> 51:55.394
You and me.

51:57.354 --> 52:00.023
Gear down. Let's go.
Lose your rifle. Come on.

52:01.358 --> 52:04.252
Man, always sitting
and babysitting the Muji.

52:04.277 --> 52:08.824
Hey, Corporal? You take care
of her. You understand me?

52:09.282 --> 52:10.367
Yes, sir.

52:11.868 --> 52:14.846
All right, Corporal,
listen to me now.

52:14.871 --> 52:20.210
I want you to stay behind me and
just be patient. All right?

52:22.212 --> 52:24.256
All right. Come on,
let's go have some fun.

52:52.200 --> 52:53.260
(GRUNTS)

52:53.285 --> 52:54.928
You all right?
Yeah.

52:54.953 --> 52:56.138
All right.

52:56.163 --> 52:57.764
I want you to start
movin' forward

52:57.789 --> 53:00.642
and I'm gonna flank around and go on
the right hand side. You hear me?

53:00.667 --> 53:01.893
I'll come with you.

53:01.918 --> 53:03.770
No. I move better alone.

53:03.795 --> 53:06.440
Now, listen, I want you
to keep this field of view.

53:06.465 --> 53:08.049
When you see me hit him,

53:08.175 --> 53:10.652
I want you to come in hard and fast.
All right.

53:10.677 --> 53:15.265
Now, no gunfire. We do this hand-to-hand.
There's too much enemy.

53:18.477 --> 53:20.270
See you in a minute.

53:51.134 --> 53:52.552
You got this.

54:22.999 --> 54:24.334
(SPEAKING LOCAL LANGUAGE)

54:27.337 --> 54:29.005
(GRUNTING)

54:34.636 --> 54:36.471
(BOTH GRUNTING)

54:43.311 --> 54:44.688
(GRUNTING)

54:58.034 --> 54:59.661
(SHOUTING IN LOCAL LANGUAGE)

55:13.842 --> 55:14.885
Ah!

55:16.052 --> 55:17.053
Oh!

55:19.723 --> 55:20.891
(GRUNTING)

55:32.611 --> 55:33.653
(GROANING)

55:45.081 --> 55:46.791
(PANTING)

55:49.836 --> 55:51.296
(PANTING)

56:00.847 --> 56:02.098
FOX: Good job.

56:23.536 --> 56:25.580
Keep your eyes down range.

56:26.665 --> 56:30.168
Anoosh, get a drink.
Get a drink.

56:37.842 --> 56:39.177
(SIGHS)

56:51.147 --> 56:52.691
Don't do it, Corporal.

56:53.233 --> 56:55.335
What's that, Senior Chief?

56:55.360 --> 56:56.820
Overthink it.

56:58.363 --> 56:59.572
Killing.

57:02.242 --> 57:06.371
Let me tell you somethin'. Every
day we go out, it's life or death.

57:07.163 --> 57:08.748
It's him or you.

57:09.833 --> 57:12.669
This is my first time
out as squad leader.

57:13.962 --> 57:16.272
Before yesterday, I...

57:16.297 --> 57:19.009
I never even fired
my weapon at anybody.

57:20.051 --> 57:22.762
And I never thought
I'd have to do it that close.

57:23.221 --> 57:24.889
It's all the same.

57:28.184 --> 57:30.328
They died today.

57:30.353 --> 57:31.813
And we lived.

57:33.648 --> 57:35.025
Look at me.

57:36.526 --> 57:38.153
Today was a good day.

57:41.197 --> 57:44.617
Now, I want you
to do something for me.

57:45.326 --> 57:47.912
I want you to get out
of your head and focus.

57:49.539 --> 57:51.541
Focus on the mission.

57:53.334 --> 57:55.045
The mission is God.

57:59.883 --> 58:01.051
All right.

58:05.388 --> 58:08.016
I'm gonna give you another
second and then we gotta go.

58:08.558 --> 58:10.560
Soto, start gearin' up.

58:15.356 --> 58:16.691
Let's go.

58:21.237 --> 58:23.465
You speak very good English.

